                <!-- Stage 7 - Highlighted with Toggle -->
                <div class="stage-large">
                    <div class="stage-header" onclick="toggleStage(7)">
                        <span class="stage-number">7</span>
                        <span class="stage-title">Outline</span>
                        <span class="toggle-icon" id="toggle-7">‚ñº</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stage-details" id="details-7">
                        <span class="ai-skill-label">AI SKILLS</span>
                        <div class="skill-description">
                            <strong>Outline Check / Bias Interrogation:</strong> Before drafting, pause and ask the AI: "Based on this outline, what will readers assume my bias is? Whose story is getting told, and whose isn't?"
                            <br><br>
                            This is your chance to examine the subjective choices you're making in structure and emphasis before they're baked into the full draft.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Stage 8 - Highlighted with Toggle -->
                <div class="stage-large">
                    <div class="stage-header" onclick="toggleStage(8)">
                        <span class="stage-number">8</span>
                        <span class="stage-title">Draft (with ongoing fact-checking)</span>
                        <span class="toggle-icon" id="toggle-8">‚ñº</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stage-details" id="details-8">
                        <span class="ai-skill-label">AI SKILLS</span>
                        <div class="skill-description">
                            <strong>Claim and Assumption Categorization:</strong> Once you've completed your draft, ask the AI to conduct a claim identification analysis. Have it identify:
                            <ul>
                                <li>What claims are you making?</li>
                                <li>What assumptions underlie those claims?</li>
                                <li>What perspective or angle is centered?</li>
                                <li>What weight is given to different stakeholders?</li>
                            </ul>
                            This helps you see the subjective choices you've made and decide if they align with your intentions.
                        </div>
                        <div class="mishap-alert">
                            <strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Watch Out:</strong> AI Off the Rails - Fact-check AI's analysis against your actual sources. If it's making incorrect claims about your draft, feed it better context.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

